quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,82,"Those who have iman and do not mix up their iman with any wrongdoing, they are the ones who are safe; it is they who are guided.´"
  6,83,"This is the argument We gave to Ibrahim against his people. We raise in rank anyone We will. Your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,84,"We gave him Ishaq and Ya´qub, each of whom We guided. And before him We had guided Nuh. And among his descendants were Dawud and Sulayman, and Ayyub, Yusuf, Musa and Harun. That is how We recompense the good-doers"
  6,85,"And Zakariyya, Yahya, ´Isa and Ilyas. All of them were among the salihun"
  6,86,"And Isma´il, al-Yasa´, Yunus and Lut. All of them We favoured over all beings"
  6,87,"And some of their forebears, descendants and brothers; We chose them and guided them to a straight path"
  6,88,"That is Allah´s guidance. He guides by it those of His slaves He wills. If they had associated others with Him, nothing they did would have been of any use"
  6,89,"They are the ones to whom We gave the Book, Judgement and Prophethood. If these people reject it We have already entrusted it to a people who did not"
  6,90,"They are the ones Allah has guided, so be guided by their guidance. Say, ´I do not ask you for any wage for it. It is simply a reminder to all beings.´"